claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A table comparing vaccine effectiveness (VE) percentages (with 95% confidence intervals) of recombinant quadrivalent influenza vaccine (RIV4), standard-dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine (SD-IIV4), and a combined RIV4 + high-dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine + adjuvanted influenza vaccine in two age groups (18–64 years and ≥65 years), with subgroups for overall, males, and females. This table reports clinical vaccine effectiveness data and does not provide any information on hemagglutinin antigen content or direct immunogenicity measurements; it does not support the claim. Note: Limited to visible table data; no information on antigen content or immunogenicity assays is provided.
